  "time_ut": 1662309124,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 138 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "138 crores will have to be paid to the officials of the fertilizer ship",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In connection with the loss of more than 138 crore rupees (US$ 6.9 million) to the government by releasing funds without any security for ninety-six thousand metric tons of organic fertilizer with harmful bacteria (Chinese Fertilizer Ship), the relevant responsible persons will be sued and recovered. As recommended by the Auditor General of the Government.",
        "Also, the Auditor General has also informed that the relevant fertilizer supplier company will be blacklisted and legal action will be taken against the supplier regarding receiving money for the unsupplied fertilizer and making a loss by not providing the required fertilizer for the 2020-21 season as per the agreement.",
        "The Auditor General has issued this recommendation after presenting the special audit report on the procurement process of 96,000 metric tons of organic fertilizers.",
        "The Auditor General has indicated in that report that there was an attempt to enter Sri Lanka in this way with fertilizers containing destructive bacteria that are not biocided and do not have any recommended agrochemicals to suppress them.",
        "The audit report stating that if this fertilizer had entered the country could have had a severe impact on the crops with economic value in Sri Lanka, the audit report also states that a loss has been caused by not providing the necessary fertilizer for paddy cultivation in the high season of 2021-22.",
        "The Auditor General also mentions that the entire amount paid for the unsupplied fertilizers has been lost.",
        "The report has made accusations against the members of the Technology Evaluation Committee, the members of the Procurement Committee, the Secretary of the Ministry of Agriculture, the Additional Secretary, the Committee consisting of the Standards Officers appointed by the Ministry Secretary.",
        "The procurement committee appointed by the Cabinet had recommended the purchase of 96,000 metric tons of fertilizer from China's Kindao Biotech Group Company and the Minister of Agriculture to obtain the approval of the Cabinet to purchase sixty percent of the recommended stock of fertilizer from Ceylon Fertilizer Company Limited and forty percent from Commercial Fertilizer Company Limited. The audit report also shows that the Cabinet Memorandum FO /61/2021 was submitted on August 5, 2021.",
        "It also states that the Cabinet had approved the memorandum on August 18, 2021.",
        "The Chinese ship carrying the cargo of organic fertilizers with harmful bacteria had reached Sri Lankan waters on 23 September 2021. A controversial situation was created as non-biodegradable organic fertilizers could not be brought into the country according to the Plant Quarantine Act and the fertilizer was not allowed to be brought into the country.",
        "This Chinese ship, which was anchored in the Sri Lankan coast for several months, left the Sri Lankan coast after paying the relevant amount."
      ],
